    PHP_CodeBrowser


    1. Structure
    2. Installation
    3. Usage
    4. View the results
    5. Contact information


1. Structure
------------------------------------------------------------------------

    |--> bin/           PHP_CodeBrowser scripts
    |--> src/           Source files for PHP_CodeBrowser
    |   |--> Plugins/   Plugins for different error handling/types
    |
    |--> templates/     Template files for PHP_CodeBrowser 
    |   |--> css/       Used CSS by templates, Color definition for errors
    |   |--> img/       Used images for PHP_CodeBrowser
    |   |--> js/        Used javascript for PHP_CodeBrowser
    |
    |--> tests/         PHPUnit test suite 
    |
    |--> LICENCE        Licence information
    |--> README         Structure and install information


2. Installation
------------------------------------------------------------------------

    a) Copy files
    ==============
    A installation is also possible by copying the svn export (ressource)
    directly to the installation folder. 
    The needed structure / files are:

    |--> bin/         
    |--> src/         
    |   |--> Plugins/ 
    |--> templates/

    b) Using the script
    ===================
    php install.php linux|win /path/to/my/installation/folder 


3. Usage
------------------------------------------------------------------------

    There are several ways and needed conditions for using PHP_CodeBrowser. 
    The ouput folder has to exists, the xml error files should match the 
    project source (do not use old files or xml files genereated from a 
    different source).
    The xml error file must match the attributes used in Plugin errors.

    a) Usage on a Windows system
    =========================
    phpcb.bat /generated/xml/error/files /path/to/project/source /path/to/ouput/folder

    b) Usage on a Linux system
    =======================
    phpcb /generated/xml/error/files /path/to/project/source /path/to/ouput/folder

    c) Call PHP_Codebrowser directly
    ================================
    php phpcb.php --xml /path/to/merged/errors.xml --source /path/to/project/source --ouput /path/to/output/folder

    If option c) will be used please assure that the used xml file is a 
    proper merge of desired xml error log files in the following format: 
    
    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
    <codebrowser>
        <error-type1>
            ...
        </error-type1>
        <error-type2>
            ...
    </codebrowser>


4. View the results
------------------------------------------------------------------------

    PHP_CodeBrowser will handle all files that have known errors.
    For each file an own view is generated. 
    
    Open the file /path/to/output/folder/treeView.html in your webbrowser.
    

